<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/4–251: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to
                                the Torquay Conference</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Torquay</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-02">April 2,
                                1951—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>638. <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> on March 31 after giving full
                            consideration to all aspects of problem raised by UK refusal improve
                            offers, including obviously undesirable consequences of failure of
                            negots, instructed negotiating team to terminate US-UK negots. This done
                            today, effective Mar 31.</p>
                        <p>Results or lack of results Torquay not public info until May 9.</p>
                        <p>Sent Dept 638, rptd info London 251.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Corse</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>